es to apply to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"individual annotations."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapviewdelegate","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNUserLocation":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnuserlocation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNUserLocation","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNUserLocation"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The MLNUserLocation class defines a specific type of annotation that identifies"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user’s current location. You do not create instances of this class"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directly. Instead, you retrieve an existing "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNUserLocation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"userLocation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property of the map view displayed in your application."}],"title":"MLNUserLocation","kind":"symbol"}}}